The paper discusses the use of human computation and machine learning in text classification tasks, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also focuses on natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as text classification (cs.CL) and information retrieval (IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of AI techniques such as machine learning (cs.AI) to improve the accuracy of text classification tasks. Finally, the paper discusses the cognitive demands of the task, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
